The paper deals with the task of referring expression grounding, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel end-to-end network architecture, which involves deep learning techniques and adaptive mechanisms, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of weakly supervised learning, which involves learning from limited or noisy data, making it relevant to sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
